<SLUG> BC-Sports-Baseball-NL Roundup, 1st Ld-2nd Add,0156 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CINCINNATI: game this season.
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Diamondbacks 6, Mets 1 &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   In Phoenix, Omar Daal, fast becoming the young ace of the
Arizona pitching staff, limited New York to two hits in eight
innings and Travis Lee broke out of a slump with his 20th home run.
	   Mets' pitchers walked 10 batters and New York committed two
errors, one by second baseman Carlos Baerga with the bases loaded
in the fifth, to drop a half-game behind Chicago in the NL
wild-card chase.
	   Daal (6-7) gave up only Jermaine Allensworth's leadoff home run
and Mike Piazza's one-out double, both in the fourth. The two hits
allowed were a franchise low. The Venezuelan left-hander has given
up six earned runs in his last five starts.
	   Hideo Nomo (5-10) gave up four runs, three earned, and allowed
just three hits in five innings but walked five, two apiece in the
first and fifth innings.
	    &UR; END
</TEXT>
