<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Vietnam-Food Poisoning </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Nearly 100 people sick in Vietnam after eating rice cakes
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HANOI, Vietnam (AP) _ Nearly 100 people, mostly children, came
down with food poisoning after eating rice cakes at a shop that
opened two days earlier, a local official said Monday.
	   Forty were hospitalized at the Thai Nguyen provincial general
hospital in northern Vietnam on Saturday, the official said. All
had been released by Sunday. Police were investigating the cause of
the incident.
	   Food poisoning is common in Vietnam, where pesticides often are
used to protect vegetables.
	   Earlier this year, more than 500 workers of a private company in
southern Dong Nai province were hospitalized after contracting food
poisoning in the company's canteen. 	   
</TEXT>
