<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Cambodia-Monks Beaten </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Cambodian villagers beat and tear robes off two Buddhist monks
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PHNOM PENH, Cambodia (AP) _ Angry villagers tore the saffron
robes off two Buddhist monks and savagely beat them for allegedly
stealing about dlrs 600, a report said Monday.
	   Khoung Saothanh, deputy chief monk of Sumpong Phal pagoda just
outside of Phnom Penh, told the Cambodia Daily the pair were left
in charge of funds for a festival, but squandered the cash.
	   Police allegedly came to the pagoda to arrest the two monks,
Roth Tanak and Roth Chouk Chinda, but stood by as incensed
villagers handed down their own punishment.
	   One monk, Thath Lock, after watching the beating, called it
``completely against the rule of Buddhist principles,'' the paper
said. 	   
</TEXT>
