<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Russia-Ruble </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Russia devalues ruble
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ After weeks of financial turmoil, Russia announced
Monday that it will devalue the shaky national currency, the ruble.
	   The Central Bank has revised the corridor in which it supports
the ruble, from about 6.3 to the dollar to 9.5 to the dollar, the
Interfax news agency reported.
	   The government also imposed a 90-day moratorium on the payment
of ruble-denominated foreign debt.
	   A ruble devaluation has been widely rumored, in part because the
government faces heavy debt payments in coming days and weeks.
	   Additional details were not immediately available.
	   (mr)
</TEXT>
