<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Lesotho-Violence </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Report: gunfire wounds two in Lesotho demonstrations
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MASERU, Lesotho (AP) _ Shots were fired during demonstrations
outside the royal palace of this tiny mountain kingdom Monday and
at least two people were injured, South African Broadcasting Corp.
radio said.
	   Crowds have been gathering outside the palace and Parliament for
the past two weeks. Protesters charged that May elections returning
the Lesotho Congress for Democracy were rigged.
	   At least two people have died and four others were injured in
previous clashes between opposition groups and supporters of the
governing party.
	   Security forces have generally been keeping a low profile during
the unrest. Opposition demonstrators have been blocking off roads,
and many shops and offices closed their doors.
	   Lesotho, with a population of 2 million, is surrounded by South
Africa.
	   (djw)	   
</TEXT>
