<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Netherlands-Asylum Center Fire </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Five burned, one seriously, in fire at Dutch refugee center
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LEEUWARDEN, Netherlands (AP) _ Fire swept through a center
housing refugees seeking asylum early Monday. Five people were
burned, one seriously.
	   Authorities in this northern Dutch city said 80 people were
evacuated from the center, which processes applications for asylum
from Asians, Africans, Turks and others seeking permission to stay
in the Netherlands.
	   Dutch television reported heavy smoke and water damage to the
facility, and that one of the victims suffered serious burns. An
investigation was under way to determine the cause of the fire.
	   (bk) 	   
</TEXT>
