<HEADLINE>
U.S. Embassy OKs dlrs 25,000 in drought aid
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HANOI, Vietnam (AP) _ U.S. Ambassador Pete Peterson has
authorized a dlrs 25,000 donation for aid to drought-stricken areas
in central Vietnam, the U.S. Information Service said Monday.
	   ``The U.S. Embassy will work with appropriate Vietnamese,
international and non-governmental organizations to determine the
areas of greatest need to distribute the assistance,'' a USIS
statement said.
	   Fourteen provinces in the country's midsection have been hit
hard by the second drought this year. In addition, an outbreak of
dengue fever also has swept across the area.
</TEXT>
