<SLUG> BC-Vietnam-Graft </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Official sentenced to eight years
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HANOI, Vietnam (AP) _ A Ho Chi Minh City official has been
sentenced to eight years in jail for embezzling money from the
hunger-elimination and poverty-alleviation fund, a court official
said Monday.
	   Luu My Hoa, 44, chairwoman of District 5's Precinct 10 for three
years until her removal in August 1996, was convicted Saturday of
taking 420 million dong (dlrs 32,000) _ a huge amount in a country
where the average annual per capita income is about dlrs 300.
	   The Communist Party and central government have launched a
campaign to ensure citizen rights. Local governments are required
to have transparency in their finances.
	   The campaign was sparked by local corruption that has led to
unrest in several provinces in the last two years.
</TEXT>
