<SLUG> BC-SKorea-Rain </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Six more deaths in weekend rains that hit southern South Korea
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SEOUL, South Korea (AP) _ Torrential rains continued to buffet
South Korea over the weekend, causing six new deaths in the
populous southern coastal regions, anti-disaster officials said
Monday.
	   The latest deaths increased to 271 the total number of dead in
two weeks of downpours that began to hit South Korea in early
August. Over 160,000 people were left homeless and property damage
was estimated at dlrs 2 billion.
	   The latest deaths included four people who were buried in a
landslide. One man died when his car fell into a rain-swollen river
and another was swept into a flooded ditch.
	   Weather officials said the strong rain fronts were swept in from
China.
	   A week before the two-week deluge began, 57 people were killed
and 29 went missing in flash floods raging down mountain valleys in
the southern tip of the Korean peninsula. 	   
</TEXT>
