<HEADLINE>
Dollar rises, Gold falls
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The U.S. dollar rose against other major
currencies in early European trading Monday. Gold prices fell.
	   Dollar rates compared with late Friday:
	   _ 1.8029 German marks, up from 1.7904
	   _ 146.19 Japanese yen, up from 145.13
	   _ 1.5033 Swiss francs, up from 1.4938
	   _ 6.0330 French francs, up from 5.9999
	   _ 2.0298 Dutch guilders, up from 2.0188
	   _ 1,774.98 Italian lire, up from 1765.60
	   _ 1.5206 Canadian dollars, up from 1.5170
	   The British pound was quoted at dlrs 1.6101, down from dlrs
1.6254.
	   London dealers fixed a recommended gold price of dlrs 283.30 bid
per troy ounce at midmorning, down from the closing price of dlrs
284.20 bid Friday.
	   In Zurich the bid price was dlrs 283.00, down from dlrs 283.70
late Friday.
	   Financial markets in Hong Kong were closed Monday for a holiday.
	   Silver opened in London at dlrs 5.13 bid troy ounce, up from
dlrs 5.12 bid Friday.
