r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Cambodia-SchoolCheats     08-17 0210
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Cambodia-School Cheats </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Cambodian police deployed to prevent cheating on high school exams
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PHNOM PENH, Cambodia (AP) _ Hundreds of armed police were
deployed in front of high schools in Cambodia's capital Monday to
prevent rampant cheating on this year's final exams.
	   ``We requested the police forces to protect and prevent
cheating,'' said Oum Hoeung, the director of Phnom Penh
municipality's education department. ``We are determined to make
the exam cleaner this year.''
	   Exam cheating has become a blatant, almost accepted, annual
ritual in Cambodia in recent years.
	   More than 8,000 12th grade students began their exams Monday.
For those who want to go to the university, passing the test is
crucial.
	   Family and friends have been known to scale school walls to
deliver cheat sheets to the exam takers or to attach crib sheets to
rocks, throwing them in through opened windows.
	   Underpaid teachers and police turn a blind eye to the practice
in exchange for small bribes.
	   Several students' siblings tried to bribe their way onto the
school premises Monday in order to find out the exam questions and
work with friends and relatives on the outside to send the answers
back in. But only a few claimed success.
</TEXT>
