<SLUG> BC-Russia-Attack </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Russian military building shelled in Caucasus
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Unidentified attackers fired a grenade launcher at
a government building in southern Russia, a news agency said
Monday.
	   Two shells crashed into the Russian Interior Ministry building
late Sunday night in the Kabardino-Balkaria region, 1,400
kilometers (900 miles) south of Moscow, the Interfax news agency
said.
	   No one was injured, and the damage to a criminal police chief's
office and a room occupied by duty officers was minimal, Interfax
said.
	   Kabardino-Balkaria borders the restive republic of Chechnya, and
has seen spillover violence following its neighbor's 1994-96
independence war against Russia.
