w1406 &Cx1f; wstm-
u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Lesotho-Violence 1stLd-Writethru   08-17 0319
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Lesotho-Violence, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Report: gunfire kills two in Lesotho demonstrations
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with reports of deaths

<TEXT>
	   MASERU, Lesotho (AP) _ Shots were fired during demonstrations
outside the royal palace of this tiny mountain kingdom Monday, and
there were conflicting reports about casualties.
	   Khauhelo Raditapole, a spokeswoman for the opposition
Basotholand Congress Party, said police opened fire early in the
morning, killing a young man and a 16-year-old girl, the South
African Press Association reported.
	   At least 30 people were injured, the spokeswoman said.
	   The British ambassador, High Commissioner Peter Smith, disputed
the report. Reached by telephone from Johannesburg, Smith said
police trying to remove barricades shot anti-riot pellets when
demonstrators threw rocks at them. Three demonstrators were
slightly injured, he said.
	   In a later incident, protesters opened fire on officers,
wounding five, Smith said.
	   Government officials could not immediately be reached.
	   The opposition had called for a general strike in Maseru for
Monday, but Smith said it was only partially successful.
	   ``The town, apart from the problems this morning, is
surprisingly more normal than I thought it would be,'' Smith said.
	   Crowds have been gathering outside the palace and Parliament for
the past two weeks. Protesters charged that May elections returning
the Lesotho Congress for Democracy were rigged.
	   At least two people have died and four others were injured in
previous clashes between opposition groups and supporters of the
governing party.
	   Previously, security forces generally kept a low profile during
the unrest. Opposition demonstrators have been blocking off roads,
and many shops and offices closed their doors.
	   Lesotho, with a population of 2 million, is surrounded by South
Africa and frequently the site of unrest.
	   (djw) 	   
</TEXT>
