<SLUG> BC-Greece-Helicopters </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Greece to buy four search and rescue helicopters
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Greece Monday will sign a deal with the
French-German Eurocopter consortium to buy four search and rescue
helicopters.
	   The 18 billion drachma (dlrs 59.4 million) deal will be signed
by the Merchant Marine Ministry for the all-weather ``Super Puma''
helicopters. The ministry is responsible for the coast guard and
port police.
	   The helicopters will mostly be used for operations in the Aegean
Sea. Helicopters are often used for medical evacuations from the
hundreds of islands that speckle the sea, also a favorite
destination for hundreds of thousands of foreign vacationers every
summer.
	   Rescue operation are currently conducted by the military.
