<HEADLINE>
Road accidents leave 54 dead in Spain
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MADRID, Spain (AP) _ Fifty-four people died and 42 suffered
serious injuries in road accidents over a busy holiday weekend in
Spain, the government said Monday.
	   Highways were packed with people heading out on vacation or
returning from their holidays.
	   The congestion was compounded by motorists making trips to take
in street festivals held Saturday as towns all over Spain honored
their patron saints.
	   The worst single accident occurred in the central province of
Albacete when a car swerved off the road after one of its tires
burst. All five people in the car were killed, the National Traffic
Directorate said.
