<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Investment </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Foreign investment in Ukraine tops dlrs 500 million in first half
</HEADLINE>
of 1998 &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ Foreign investment in Ukraine totaled dlrs
517.7 million in the first half of 1998, up 54.3 percent from the
same period last year, a news report said Monday.
	   As of July 1, total foreign investment in Ukraine since the
nation became independent was dlrs 2.47 billion, the Interfax news
agency said, citing the State Statistics Committee.
	   Nearly one-fifth of that amount, dlrs 428.9 million, came from
the United States, followed by the Netherlands, Germany, South
Korea, Great Britain and Cyprus.
	   Ukraine, which became independent in 1991, has lagged behind
other former Soviet bloc nations in attracting foreign money as it
has been slow to implement structural reforms needed to attract
outside investors.
	   (vl/nw/mr)
</TEXT>
