<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Iran-Drugs </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Iranian authorities seize 4.8 kilograms of heroin
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TEHRAN, Iran (AP) _ Police seized 4.8 kilograms (10.5 pounds) of
heroin and arrested four men, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported Monday.
	   It said the drugs were concealed in a vehicle in the central
Yazd province and two Afghans, a Pakistani and an Iranian were
arrested.
	   Large drug hauls are common in Iran, which lies along a route
used by smugglers in neighboring Pakistan and Afghanistan to
transport drugs such as opium, hashish and heroin to Gulf Arab
states and beyond.
	   Drug smugglers face the death penalty under Iranian law.
Hundreds have been hanged since the law was passed nine years ago.
 &UR; ti-ggl
</TEXT>
