R I &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Greece-Drugs     08-17 0222
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Greece-Drugs </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Drugs allegedly found inside man with forged Dutch passport
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PROMAHONAS, Greece (AP) _ A man traveling on a forged Dutch
passport was arrested on the border with Bulgaria Monday after an
x-ray showed he had swallowed 12 condoms believed filled with
heroin.
	   Police and local media said the man was carrying a forged Dutch
passport in the name Gregory Edward, 27, when he was arrested by
customs officials on the border aboard a train headed from the
Bulgarian capital of Sofia to Athens.
	   ``He is not being cooperative. He is not giving us any
information,'' said Dimitris Inos, a regional police chief.
	   According to local medical examiner Minas Georgiades, the man
had swallowed 12 egg-shaped condoms containing 212 grams (7.5
ounces) of a substance believed to be heroin. Chemical tests were
being conducted.
	   Drug traffic across Bulgaria and other Balkan states has surged
after border regulations were eased following the collapse of the
Communist system in 1989.
	   Customs officials at Bulgaria's Black Sea port of Varna seized
670 kilograms (1,474 pounds) of cocaine loaded in a cargo container
last Friday. Greek customers officers on the same day arrested two
Albanians on the border with Turkey after finding 26 kilograms (57
pounds) of heroin in their car.
 &UR; pq	   
</TEXT>
