<HEADLINE>
Nine people die in car crash
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CAIRO, Egypt (AP) _ Nine people were killed Monday when a truck
crashed into a mini-bus pulling onto a narrow rural road outside
Cairo, police said.
	   Three others were seriously wounded in the accident in
El-Mansouria village, some 15 kilometers (9 miles) south of Cairo,
a police official said, speaking on customary condition of
anonymity.
	   The dead were identified as members of two families riding in
the minibus and its driver.
	   Police said they were questioning the truck driver, who was
believed to be speeding.
