<HEADLINE>
Two Egyptian consturction workers killed in accident
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KUWAIT (AP) _ Two Egyptian construction workers were killed when
a wall collapsed on them while they worked, the Interior Ministry
said Monday.
	   Ministry spokesman Col. Bader Saleh identified the men as
Mohammad Ahmed Abdul-Hamid, 60, and Abdul-Razzak Mohammad Ahmed,
51.
	   The accident took place Sunday in the Kuwait City suburb of
Bneid al-Gar, he said.
