<SLUG> BC-EU_NIreland Reaction </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
With NIrelend-Arrests
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EU's Santer: Omagh blast must not derail Ulster peace process &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) _ European Commission President Jacques
Santer said Monday the blast in Omagh that killed 28 and wounded
220 must not derail the peace process in Northern Ireland.
	   In a statement, Santer expressed his ``very deep shock and
dismay'' at the bombing.
	   ``We extend our deepest sympathy to all the families and
frioednds of those kille,'' he added on behalf of the 20-member EU
executive Commission.
	   Santer said the bombing must not halt peace efforts.
	   ``We believe unequivocally that supporting the peace process is
the only way forward toward lasting peace and reconcilliation'' in
Northern Ireland, he added.
