<HEADLINE>
Prosecutor interrogates former Juventus star Gianluca Vialli
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; RETRANSMITTING to correct category code &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   TURIN, Italy (AP) _ Former Juventus star Gianluca Vialli met
Monday with a prosecutor looking into allegations that he and other
players in Italy's top division soccer league took
performance-enhancing substances.
	   Vialli, now player-coach of English club Chelsea, was summoned
after AS Roma coach Zdenek Zeman told Italian media he was amazed
by the quick muscular development of players including Vialli and
Alessandro Del Piero, a star forward for Juventus.
