<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Thailand-Bank Protest </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Employees of doomed Thai bank stage protest
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; AP Photo BK102

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ More than 500 employees of a bank being
shut down by the government protested the move Monday, saying they
will lose their livelihoods.
	   An estimated 5,000 people will lose their jobs when Bangkok Bank
of Commerce completely ceases operations by the end of next year.
It has already been suspended from most banking activities as part
of a sweeping restructuring of the debt-laden banking system
announced by the government on Friday.
	   Angry over the impending layoffs, bank employees demanded the
government provide them with financial aid or find them new jobs.
	   ``Some of us have been working for the bank for 20 years, does
the government care what will happen to my family? How could I find
a job at this age?'' said a protester in his early forties.
	   Employees in provincial branches have flooded the bank's
headquarter's with thousands of phone calls, expressing their fears
of being jobless in the midst of Thailand's worst economic crisis
in decades.
	   ``I don't know what to do. I have family to feed, and house and
car loans to pay off,'' said another employee.
</TEXT>
