<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-France-Lama </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Goalkeeper Lama to make international comeback against Austria
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ Goalkeeper Bernard Lama joined the French soccer
squad that flew to Vienna Monday and is a definite starter for this
week's match against Austria.
	   Lama, 35, replaces France's first choice goalkeeper Fabien
Bathez, who injured his left thigh playing for Monaco on Saturday.
	   Lama, who this year moved back to Paris Saint-Germain after a
spell at England's West Ham, won the last of his 37 international
caps against Morocco in May.
	   Although Lama was not in the original squad named last week for
Wednesday's match against Austria in Vienna, Roger Lemerre,
France's new coach, said he remains Bathez's deputy.
	   Lama's call up was the only change to Lemerre's squad for
France's first match since it won the World Cup in July.
	   (ae-ip)
</TEXT>
