<HEADLINE>
BC-Sports-Soccer-Iran-Mahfdaviakia Accident
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Iranian soccer star suffers head injury in car accident

<TEXT>
	   TEHRAN, Iran (AP) _ Iranian soccer star Mehdi Mahdavikia was
injured along with his wife when his car hit a tree in the Caspian
province of Mazandaran, the official Islamic Republic News Agency
reported Monday.
	   Mahdavikia, who scored the winning goal against the United
States in this year's World Cup, suffered head injuries in Sunday's
accident in the provincial capital of Chalous, the agency said. His
wife suffered leg injuries.
	   No other vehicles were involved in the accident, which occurred
as Mahdavikia was returning to Tehran from a summer vacation.
	   Mahdavikia, 22, and his wife were reported to be in stable
condition in hospital and were visited by a number of fans as well
as the mayor and governor of Chalous.
	   Following a standout performance in Iran's three World Cup
matches, Mahdavikia was tipped to join a number of European clubs,
including England's Tottenham Hotspur, Holland's Ajax, Italy's
Inter Milan or Hamburg of Germany. But his local club Piroozi has
yet to release him.
	   In 1997, Mahdavikia was named Asia's Young Player of the Year.
