<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Russia </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Presidents of Ukraine, Russia may meet informally this week
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) - Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma and his
Russian counterpart Boris Yeltsin have reached a preliminary
agreement to meet informally in Yeltsin's residence near Moscow
this week, a top Ukraianian official said Monday.
	   Yeltsin and Kuchma have agreed to meet in the Zavidovo residence
between Thursday and Saturday, presidential chief-of-staff Yevhen
Kushnaryov said, according to the Interfax news agency.
	   He said the two sides have already finalized a list of questions
the two presidents are to discuss, most of them concerning economic
cooperation.
	   Last month, Yeltsin and Kuchma agreed to hold a summit in the
eastern Ukrainian city of Kharkiv on Sept. 18-19 with large
government delegations participating.
	   Ukrainian government officials have since indicated that the two
presidents might have another meeting before that date.
	   In February, the two leaders signed an ambitious economic
cooperation plan, and Yeltsin said that there were ``no unsettled
problems'' left between the two nations.
	   However, there has been discord over Russian customs taxes on
Ukrainian goods and there have been frictions in recent years over
issues such as control of the Black Sea naval bases from the Soviet
era and Ukraine's natural gas debts to Russia.
	   Also, the Russian parliament has failed to ratify a friendship
treaty that was signed last year.
	   (vl/ji) 	   
</TEXT>
