<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Greece-Traffic Accidents </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Record traffic deaths mar holiday weekend
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Greece's police chief Monday ordered a
nationwide crackdown on traffic violators after a record 41 people
were killed and 458 injured in 302 accidents during the holiday
weekend.
	   Gen. Athanasios Vasilopoulos ordered police around the country
to increase patrols on the nation's highways and ``to be especially
strict with violators.''
	   Extra measures include more random road blocks, alcohol tests
and speed traps.
	   Accidents deaths during the weekend Assumption of the Virgin
holiday, one of the most important in Greece, were considerably
higher than those during the four-day Orthodox Easter exodus
earlier this year.
	   During that holiday, 35 motorists were killed and about 500
injured. Two years ago, a record 36 people died during the annual
Easter exodus and return.
	   Greece and Portugal have the highest road death records in
Europe.
