<SLUG> BC-India-Kashmir, 1st Ld-Writethru,0223 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
14 people killed in Kashmir
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES throughout with Muslim militants killing four
civilians in Kashmir &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   SRINAGAR, India (AP) _ A total of 14 people were killed in
troubled Kashmir on Monday in a clash between army troops and
Muslim separatist guerrillas and in rebel attacks on civilians,
Indian officials said.
	   Ten rebels were killed in an encounter shortly after midnight in
the dense forests in the Kupwara district, 140 kilometers (85
miles) north of summer capital Srinagar, said an army spokesman who
cannot be identified. There were no casualties among the soldiers.
	   In the same district, militants killed two brothers in their
home. Both were activists of the National Conference party, which
governs Jammu-Kashmir state, police said.
	   In a separate incident, militants abducted three civilians in
the Baramulla district after midnight and abandoned their bodies a
few hours later, said the police control room in Srinagar.
	   In the last 15 days, some 30 militants have been killed in
encounters in Kupwara district following an increase in patrolling
by troops.
	   Army and paramilitary soldiers have been fighting Muslim
guerrillas who demand an independent Kashmir. The insurrection,
which broke out in 1989, has left more than 16,000 people dead so
far. 	   
</TEXT>
