<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Chelsea-Petrescu, 1st Ld-writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Romanian star set to leave Chelsea
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS Chelsea quotes in 6th graf, Ajax link in 9th graf
Petrescu possibly headed to Ajax

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Romanian international Dan Petrescu looks set to
become the first foreign casualty at Chelsea as Gianluca Vialli
tries to balance the budget after splashing out 12 million pounds
(dlrs 19.7 million) on players during the off-season.
	   Petrescu, who scored the winning goal in Romania's victory over
England in a World Cup group match this summer, was not named in
Chelsea's squad for its season opener against Conventry on
Saturday.
	   Chelsea, which fielded nine foreign players in its starting 11,
lost the game 2-1.
	   Vialli told the 30-year-old defender he was free to leave
Stamford Bridge, the Express newspaper reported Monday.
	   ``I am very sad,'' Petrescu was quoted as saying. ``Chelsea want
to sell me. Vialli said I will not be playing in the first XI this
year. If can find a club to go to, I will leave.''
	   Chelsea managing director Colin Hutchinson said Dutch club Ajax
had expressed interest in Petrescu.
	   ``We will not stand in the way but Ajax have not yet made a
formal bid,'' he said.
	   Hutchinson said Petrescu, who has played 100 games for Chelsea,
was one of the players for which the Blues were prepared to
consider an offer.
	   Chelsea, which has an annual salary bill exceeding 23 million
pounds (dlrs 37.4 million), was reportedly considering a 2.5
million pound (dlrs 4.1 million) offer from Ajax.
	   Veteran Welsh international Mark Hughes was the first
high-profile departure from Stamford Bridge after the Chelsea boss
signed Brian Laudrup, Pierluigi Casiraghi, Albert Ferrer and Marcel
Desailly in the off-season.
	   Hughes, who signed with Chelsea in 1995 _ the same year as
Petrescu _ transfered to Southampton.
	   Other 1997-98 first team regulars to leave this season include
Frank Sinclair and Danny Granville.
	   Petrescu, who was in Bucharest this week, has also been linked
with moves to Read Madrid. He has 60 caps for Romania. He played 31
games for Chelsea last season and scored five goals.
	   (jp)
</TEXT>
