<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) _ Malayan Banking Bhd will reduce
its base lending rate to 10.90 percent yearly from 11.40 percent
from Tuesday, the national news agency Bernama said Monday.
	   The bank said the last revision was made on Aug 7, 1998 when the
rate was reduced from 11.90 percent to 11.40 percent.
	   Another bank, Public Bank announced it will cut its base lending
rate to 11.00 percent from 11.5 percent previously in line with the
government's efforts to reduce the cost of borrowing.
	   The bank said the will help improve consumer sentiment and
spending which had fallen significantly in the past few months.
	   Bank Bumiputra Malaysia Bhd announced the reduction of its base
lending rate from 11.50 percent currently to 11.00 percent earlier
this month. 	   
