<HEADLINE>
Chinese government to give Hong Kong two giant pandas
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HONG KONG (AP) _ Mainland China will give Hong Kong two giant
pandas early next year as a gift, the Hong Kong government
announced Monday.
	   The pandas, known as Jia Jia and An An, will be housed in a
special enclosure to be built at Hong Kong's Ocean Park, a
government statement said.
	   It said the gift was a valuable opportunity for Hong Kong people
to learn about the endangered animal. Only about 1,000 pandas are
believed to remain in China.
	   Hong Kong reverted to Chinese rule last year. 	   
