<SLUG> BC-EU-Bosnia Demining </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EU's Bosnia de-mining program back on track after technical, legal
</HEADLINE>
problems &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) _ The European Commission said Monday it
has resolved technical and legal problems surrounding its funding
of a de-mining program in Bosnia and that removal of mines will
start shortly.
	   ``There were technical problems,'' said EU spokesman Costas
Verros EU to explain months of delay in removing unexploded
anti-personnel mines in Bosnia.
	   Also, he said the de-mining program fell victim to a recent EU
high court ruling forcing the European Commision to provide a legal
basis for a number of spending areas, including the mine removal
program.
	   ``New contracts have been signed and the program has been
restarted,'' said Verros.
	   In all some 700,000 mines are to be rendered harmless in a
de-mining program that was due to start last January. Already dlrs
6 million dollars have been spent to train and equip a 230-member
mine removal team.
