<SLUG> BC-Weather Summary,0980 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   Moisture left over from the tropical wave that passed through
the local area on Sunday continues across Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands in the form of frequent passing showers.
	   Thunderstorms were seen on Doppler radar and satellite imagery
over the Caribbean sea and very close to the south coast of Puerto
Rico. All of this precipitation was moving towards the
west-northwest at about 10 miles an hour.
	   The weather will improve for tonight. A weak tropical wave is
expected to pass mainly to the south of the region on Tuesday,
brushing by St. Croix and the south coast of Puerto Rico.
	   Dry and stable weather conditions with hazy skies are forecast
for Wednesday. A very strong tropical wave is expected to arrive in
the Virgin Islands Thursday and will pass through Puerto Rico
Thursday night or Friday morning.
	   San Juan and the northern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy. A 50 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms, mostly inland this afternoon. High near 90. Wind
near calm this morning, becoming east at 15 mph and gusty this
afternoon.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Slight chance for coastal thunderstorms. Low 75 to 80. Wind
northeast 5 to 10 mph.
	   Tuesday... Partly sunny with a 40 percent chance of showers and
afternoon thunderstorms. High near 90. Wind northeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Eastern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Variable cloudiness with a 50 percent chance of showers
and thunderstorms. High 85 to 95. Wind east 10 to 15 mph with
higher gusts this afternoon.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Slight chance for coastal thunderstorms. Low 75 to 80. Wind
northeast around 10 mph.
	   Tuesday... Partly sunny with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Slight chance for an afternoon thunderstorm. High 85 to 95. Wind
northeast 15 mph.
	   Ponce and the southern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Variable afternoon cloudiness with a 60 percent chance
of showers and thunderstorms. High near 90 to 95. Wind southeast 10
to 20 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy. A 20 percent chance of showers. Low 70
to 80. Wind light northeast.
	   Tuesday... Partly sunny with a 50 percent chance of showers and
afternoon thunderstorms. High 90 to 95. Wind southeast 10 to 15
mph.
	   Mayaguez and the western sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly sunny in the morning. Increasing afternoon
cloudiness with a 70 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms
some with heavy rainfall. High 85 to 90. Wind east 10 to 20 mph
except for an afternoon sea breeze along the west coast.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a slight chance of showers. Slight
chance for evening thunderstorms. Low 65 to 75. Wind east 5 to 10
mph. Chance of rain is less than 20 percent.
	   Tuesday... Partly sunny with a 50 percent chance of showers and
afternoon thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind northeast 15 mph
except for a west wind 5 to 10 mph along the west coast in the
afternoon.
	   Interior sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly sunny morning. Variable cloudiness afternoon
with a 60 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms. High from 75
to 80 mountains to 85 to 90 lower valleys. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low 65 to 70 mountains to 70 to 80 lower valleys. Wind northeast 5
to 10 mph.
	   Tuesday... Partly sunny with a 50 percent chance of showers and
afternoon thunderstorms. High from 75 to 80 mountains to 85 to 95
low elevations. Wind northeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   St. Thomas, St. John and the Adjacent Islands-St. Croix:
	   Today... Partly cloudy with a 40 percent chance of showers.
Possible thunderstorms. Becoming breezy this afternoon. High 90 to
95. Wind east 15 to 20 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Slight chance for thunderstorms. Low near 80. Wind northeast 10 to
15 mph.
	   Tuesday... Partly sunny with a 50 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms. High 90 to 95. Wind northeast 15 mph.
	   Atlantic waters north and northeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft should exercise caution.
	   This afternoon... Wind east 15 to 20 kt. Seas 4 to 5 ft.
Scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind northeast 15 to 20 kt. Seas 4 to 6 ft. Scattered
showers and isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday... Wind northeast 15 to 20 kt. Seas 4 to 5 ft. Scattered
showers. Widely scattered thunderstorms.
	   Caribbean waters south and southeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft should exercise caution.
	   This afternoon... Wind east 15 to 20 kt. Seas 4 to 6 ft.
Scattered to numerous showers. Widely scattered thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind northeast 10 to 20 kt. Seas 4 to 6 ft. Scattered
showers and isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday... Wind northeast 15 to 20 kt. Seas 4 to 5 ft. Scattered
to numerous showers. Widely scattered thunderstorms.
	   Near shore waters of western Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Wind variable mainly east 10 to 20 kt. Seas 2
to 3 ft. Widely scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind east 5 to 15 kt. Seas 2 ft. Scattered showers
and isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday... Wind northeast 10 to 20 kt. Seas 4 to 5 ft. Scattered
showers and thunderstorms.
	   Outlook for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands waters:
	   Tuesday night through Friday... Wind 20 kt or less. Seas 6 ft or
less.
</TEXT>
