<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Cantona Returns </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Cantona to captain Manchester United for the last time
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MANCHESTER, England (AP) _ Retired French soccer star Eric
Cantona will captain Manchester United one last time _ in a
testimonial match against a team named in his honor.
	   Cantona will lead his old club into the Munich Air Disaster
testimonal match at Old Trafford on Tuesday.
	   The match was arranged to mark the 40th anniversary of the air
tragedy, which claimed the lives of eight Manchester United players
in February 1958.
	   Cantona, who helped the Red Devils to four Premier League titles
in five years at the club, arrived in Manchester on Monday for the
first time since his sudden retirement 17 months ago.
	   His last game at Old Trafford was in the final game of the 1997
championship-winning campaign. He is expected to bid farewell to a
sell-out 55,000 crowd at Old Trafford.
	   The match was originally scheduled for February to coincide with
the date of the air crash but had to be postponed due to Manchester
United's FA Cup commitments.
	   Bryan Robson will lead the Cantona 11, which will also include
French striker Jean-Pierre Papin, Paul Ince, Mark Hughes, David
Batty and Gary McAllister.
	   French World Cup captain Laurent Blanc, who missed France's
historic World Cup win after being sent off in the semifinal
against Croatia, will also play for the Cantona 11.
	   (jp)
</TEXT>
