<SLUG> BC-Austria-Drugs </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Marijuana found in truck carrying herbs
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   VIENNA, Austria (AP) _ An Albanian truck carrying medicinal
herbs also was laden with almost a half-ton of marijuana, the
Austria Press Agency reported Monday.
	   After receiving a tip from Slovenian officials, customs officers
in Austria stopped the truck as it entered the country last Tuesday
at the Karawanken Tunnel, about 335 kilometers (210 miles)
southwest of the capital, Vienna, APA reported.
	   Customs officers, aided by a drug-sniffing dog, discovered the
drug stashed behind a false wall in the truck.
	   The Belgian truck driver was turned over to police. No other
details were available.
	   (scl/rp)
</TEXT>
