<SLUG> BC-France-Turkey-Arrest </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Turkish crime figure arrested in Nice
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   NICE, France (AP) _ A prominent Turkish organized crime figure
being sought for attempted murder was arrested Monday on the French
Riviera, police said.
	   Alaatin Cakici, described by police as dangerous, was arrested
in a Nice hotel along with a female companion and his bodyguard,
who was armed with a pistol, police said.
	   Acting on arrest warrants from Turkey via Interpol, about 20
officers were involved in the operation, police officials said on
customary anonymity. Turkish officials suspect Cakici of attempted
murder, they said.
	   He was being detained ahead of extradition proceedings, the
police said.
	   (parf-jn)
</TEXT>
