<SLUG> BC-Greece-Turkish Flag,0139 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Greek authorities arrest Turks for raising Turkish flag
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KALYMNOS, Greece (AP) _ Greek authorities arrested six Turks who
allegedly raised their nation's flag on a lamppost Monday during a
local festival.
	   They were released on the nearby island of Kos after misdemeanor
charges were filed for disturbing the peace, disturbing national
sentiments and leaving port without sailing permission. A March
trial was scheduled.
	   National symbols evoke strong emotions on Aegean islands near
the Turkish coast, an area where Turks have questioned Greek
sovereignty over many islets.
	   The six Turks, including a heart surgeon and a Mercedes dealer,
arrived here aboard a Turkish yacht, allegedly raised the flag,
then fled on the boat, which was intercepted by a Greek coast guard
patrol boat. 	   
</TEXT>
