<HEADLINE>
London shares close higher
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Share prices on the London Stock Exchange closed
higher Monday, as Wall Street staged a recovery.
	   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index rose 12.2
points, or 0.2 percent, to close at 5,467.2.
	   Volume was 656.2 million shares, compared with 912.3 million on
Friday.
