	   _US-CLINTON INVESTIGATION-SCENE. Kenneth Starr's engineers slip
into the courthouse toting a stainless steel case marked ``KG-104,
Secure Video.'' Up Pennsylvania Avenue, business at the White House
is practically at a standstill. Onlookers at both places seem to be
holding their breath. Has moved.
	   _ANALYSIS-US-CLINTON INVESTIGATION. Expected by 2100 GMT.
	   MOSCOW _ After spending billions of dollars over the past three
months to prop up Russia's weak currency, the government gives up
Monday and lets the ruble's value drop by a third. RUSSIA-ECONOMY.
Lead has moved. Developments will be expedited. By Judith Ingram.
AP Photos MOSB104, 106, 110-114.
	   MOSCOW _ Until it went crashing on Monday, the stable ruble had
perhaps been Boris Yeltsin's only boast, his only inarguable
economic success since the collapse of the Soviet Union.
ANALYSIS-RUSSIA-RUBLE WRECK. Has moved. By Maura Reynolds.
