<SLUG> BC-Israel-Bike Bandit, 1st ld-Writethru,0164 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Israeli bank robbing legend to get early prison release
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: FIXES typo in first word of lede &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ A businessman turned bank robber whose
motorcycle getaways were legendary in Israel during the late 1980s
will be released early for good behavior, the prison authority said
Monday.
	   Roni Liebowitz, nicknamed the ``Bikerbank,'' became a popular
cult figure after claiming that robbing banks was the only way to
maintain a decent lifestyle in Israel.
	   Liebowitz, whose trademark was firing one shot in the air before
taking off on his bike, stole over 300,000 shekels (then about dlrs
175,500) in 22 heists.
	   In 1991, he was sentenced to 20 years in prison.
	   A parole committee this week found Liebowitz to be a model
prisoner and recommended an early release, prison authority
spokeswoman Orit Messer-Harel said.
	   She said Lebovitz would be paroled Sept. 2, after having served
half his sentence. 	   
</TEXT>
