<SLUG> BC-Iraq </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Aziz briefs Cabinet of latest development with the UN
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BAGHDAD, Iraq (AP) _ Iraq's deputy prime minister briefed the
Cabinet on his talks with the envoy of U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan, the official Iraqi News Agency said Monday.
	   The Cabinet meeting was chaired by President Saddam Hussein, the
agency added.
	   It said Deputy Prime Minister Tariq Aziz briefed the Cabinet of
his talks with Prakash Shah, Annan's envoy in Baghdad.
	   It gave no further details.
	   Earlier Monday, U.N. officials said Prakash sent a letter to
Annan, keeping him up to date with his progress in Baghdad.
	   Prakash returned to Baghdad on Thursday and in a meeting with
Aziz urged Iraq to allow arms monitors to continue their
inspections.
	   Iraq froze cooperation with the United Nations after the chief
U.N. weapons inspector, Richard Butler, refused to certify that
Baghdad had destroyed its weapons of mass destruction.
	   Also Monday, Security Council members considered a
Japanese-drafted letter affirming the work of U.N. weapons
inspectors in Iraq.
