<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Iraq,0156 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Aziz briefs Cabinet of latest development with the UN
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BAGHDAD, Iraq (AP) _ Iraq's deputy prime minister briefed
President Saddam Hussein and the Iraqi Cabinet Monday on talks with
U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan's envoy, the official Iraqi News
Agency said.
	   INA gave no further deatils of Tariq Aziz's account of his talks
with Prakash Shah.
	   Earlier Monday, U.N. officials said Prakash sent a letter to
Annan with his account of his meetings.
	   Prakash arrived in Baghdad Thursday with a message from Annan
urging Iraq to allow arms monitors to continue their inspections.
	   Iraq froze cooperation with the United Nations after the chief
U.N. weapons inspector, Richard Butler, refused to certify that
Baghdad had destroyed its weapons of mass destruction.
	   Also Monday, Security Council members considered a
Japanese-drafted letter affirming the work of U.N. weapons
inspectors in Iraq. 	   
</TEXT>
