<SLUG> BC-Dollar-Gold, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Dollar higher, gold mixed
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDS: UPDATES with late rates &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The U.S. dollar was higher against other major
currencies in late European trading Monday. Gold prices were mixed.
	   Dollar rates compared with late Friday:
	   _1.7916 German marks, up from 1.7904
	   _145.72 Japanese yen, up from 145.13
	   _1.5022 Swiss francs, up from 1.4938
	   _6.0060 French francs, up from 5.9999
	   _2.0202 Dutch guilders, up from 2.0188
	   _1,766.00 Italian lire, up from 1,765.60
	   _1.5245 Canadian dollars, up from 1.5170
	   The British pound was quoted at dlrs 1.6172, down from dlrs
1.6254.
	   Gold closed in London at dlrs 284.15 bid per troy ounce, down
from the closing price of dlrs 284.20 bid Friday.
	   In Zurich gold traded at dlrs 283.80, up from dlrs 283.70.
	   Financial markets in Hong Kong were closed Monday for a holiday.
	   Silver closed in London at dlrs 5.10 bid per troy ounce, down
from dlrs 5.12 bid Friday.
	   (eml)
</TEXT>
