<HEADLINE>

</HEADLINE>
    &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  APTV'S 1800 GMT OUTLOOK FOR MONDAY 17 AUGUST 1998  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
----
For Planner / Newsdesk use - stories expected to move in the next 12
hours  &QC;  &QC; 
----
 &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; CLINTON GRAND JURY ADVISORY &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
----
President Bill Clinton has begun giving his testimony to the grand jury.
Testimony is being conducted via video link to the map room of the
White House. There will be NO MEDIA COVERAGE.
----
However, APTV will interrupt scheduled feeds with any breaking news.

The first word on what Clinton is telling the grand jury
will come from his personal lawyer, David Kendall, who is expected
to make a statement later. APTV will carry this LIVE.

Should Clinton choose to make an address to the nation,
APTV will carry this LIVE on the Global Video Wire.
