Starr leaving his house, former Commerce Secretary Mickey Kantor,
now a private lawyer, advising Clinton arriving at White House,
headlines and media stake-outs, talk show clips and the scene at the
courthouse. Updated with sketches of what Clinton may look like
while giving testimony, and voxpops. (FIRST RUN EUROPE LATE 1500)
---
NIRELAND: OMAGH 4 - Wraps the day's events in Omagh, including
comment from David Trimble, wreath laying, comment from the Rev William
McCrea, former Democratic Unionist Party MP,  David Trimble, first
minister of Northern Ireland Assembly and leader of Ulster Unionist
Party,  and stills of some of the victims. (EXPECTED NORTH AMERICA
1830)
---
NIRELAND: VICTIMS - APTV visits Enniskillen Hospital to talk to some
of the victims of Saturday's bomb blast - they describe their
memories of the horrific bomb which killed 28 people and injured
220. (FIRST RUN F-L-A-S-H 1700)
---
ESALVADOR: VOTE - A report from El Salvador as former leftist
Salvadoran guerrillas voted for their presidential candidate for the
1999 elections this weekend. (First Ran LATIN AMERICA 2130 16 Aug)
---
JAPAN: CAMERA - An APTV feature on a camcorder designed for night
filming that has an embarrassing extra ability -- when used in
daylight or with a special filter it is able to penetrate clothing.
Electronics giant Sony inadvertently invented the X-ray device.
(FIRST RUN APTV EUROVISION 1440)
---
US: FOSSETT - APTV has search and rescue footage of balloonist and
millionaire Steve Fossett in a raft in the Coral Sea off Queensland.
He was spotted eight hours after his attempt to fly around the world
ended when his balloon went down in a thunderstorm.
No Access Australia - (FIRST RUN EUROPE UPDATE 1130)
---
TAIWAN: HSINCHU - Feature on how Hsinchu Park - the world's
fourth-largest maker of semi-conductors - is weathering the Asian
financial crisis. The package includes production line footage and
soundbites from company officials who came to Hsinchu from Silicon
Valley. (FIRST RUN 0715 ASIA PACIFIC LATE)
----
INDONESIA: INDEPENDENCE - Indonesians have been celebrating their
national day amid the country's worst economic crisis in decades and
troubling rumours that renewed rioting may break out during the
festivities. APTV has  President Habibie attending the ceremony and
various honour guard marches in the palace grounds. (F-L-A-S-H 1000)
----
CHINA: INDONESIA - To coincide with Indonesia's national day,
students rallied outside the Indonesian embassy in Beijing to
protest rapes and attacks on ethnic Chinese in Indonesia
during riots in May. APTV has coverage of the protest and a press
conference by a women's pressure group. (FIRST RUN 0715 ASIA PACIFIC
LATE)
----
JAPAN: NIKKEI - The US dollar rose against the yen in early
trading, following concerns about economic stability in Russia
during Friday's trading in New York. APTV has trading footage.
(FIRST RUN 0715 ASIA PACIFIC LATE)
----
ITALY: PALIO - APTV has the footage of the traditional horse race
through the streets of Siena, which anti-rights activists call cruel
and barbaric, citing that this year's race alone left three horses
injured and one had to be put down afterwards. (FIRST RUN EUROPE
UPDATE 1130)
---
REAL IRA: FILE - While responsibility for the Omagh bomb seeming
increasingly to rest with the dissident Republican Real IRA, we
have a backgrounder. Part No Access UK. (FIRST RUN EUROPE UPDATE
1130)
---
RUSSIA: DUMA - Comment from Gennady Seleznyov, State Duma speaker
and from Gennady Zyuganov, Communist party chief on Russia's economy
woes. (FIRST RUN EUROPE UPDATE 1130GMT)
---
AUSTRALIA: MYANMAR 2 - A Sydney woman tells how she feared for her
life while being interrogated by Myanmar military police. APTV has
Alison Vicary speaking on return to Australia, supporters at airport
holding banners and cheering and shots of a student democracy
protest. Part No Access Australia. (FIRST RUN EUROPE UPDATE 1130)
