<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Israel-Palestinians, 1st Ld,0271 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Palestinian police say they are close to catching detainee
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES throughout with three taxi drivers arrested, fresh
details &QL; 
 &UR; By SAMAR ASSAD &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ Palestinian police on the trail of escaped
Hamas leader Imad Awadallah have arrested three taxi drivers who
gave him rides, the West Bank security chief said Monday.
	   Awadallah, a key figure in the Hamas military wing, escaped
Saturday from a Palestinian jail in the West Bank town of Jericho.
	   On Sunday, Palestinian security forces launched a massive
manhunt for Awadallah, conducting house-to-house searches in
Jericho and imposing a curfew.
	   The restrictions, not tightly enforced, were lifted Monday after
security officials said they were convinced Awadallah was no longer
in town.
	   ``All I can say is that he is not in Jericho,'' said Col. Jibril
Rajoub, head of the Palestinians' Preventive Security Service in
the West Bank. ``We will catch him.''
	   Rajoub said three taxi driver had been detained for giving
Awadallah a ride. Awadallah told the first driver that he needed to
get to his father who had a stroke, Rajoub said.
	   The driver took Awadallah for a short ride, but became
suspicious of him, and ordered him out somewhere in Jericho.
Awadallah spent the night in an abandoned house in Jericho, Rajoub
said and in the morning he got into another taxi which took him out
of the city.
	   Awadallah then got into a third taxi and was taken to another
destination. Rajoub did not provide further details to reporters.
 &UR; Awadallah, 29, 8th graf pvs 	   
</TEXT>
