<SLUG> BC-France-Diana Remembrance </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Most French want street or plaza named after Diana
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ As the anniversary of Princess Diana's death in
Paris approaches, 70 percent of French people want a street or
plaza to be named after her, according to a survey.
	   In the Gallup poll, to be published in Tuesday's France-Soir
newspaper, 26 percent of respondents were against the idea, and 4
percent had no opinion.
	   Diana was killed last Aug. 31 in a car crash in the Pont de
l'Alma traffic tunnel. Since then, a makeshift memorial has formed
at the nearby Flame of Liberty, originally set up to honor
French-American ties. Visitors are mainly tourists.
	   The poll was conducted by telephone Aug. 13-14 among 1,002
people over the age of 15. Margins of error for such polls are
usually plus or minus 2-3 percentage points.
	   (parf-jn)
</TEXT>
