<HEADLINE>
Croatia star Robert Jarni signs for Real Madrid
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MADRID, Spain (AP) _ Croatia's World Cup star Robert Jarni
signed a three-season contract Monday with Spanish European
Champion side Real Madrid.
	   The deal ended speculation over the future of the midfielder who
decided to leave Spanish club Betis last month and had reached a
deal to sign for English club Coventry.
	   The 29-year-old, however, changed his plans in recent weeks when
Real Madrid began expressing interest in his services.
	   Jarni arrived in the Spanish capital on Sunday and passed a
medical test early Monday after which he put his name to a
three-season contract,a club official said. There no details
available regarding the financial terms of the deal.
	   The official could not comment on whether Madrid would have to
pay any money to Coventry as part of the signing.
	   At Real, Jarni will join fellow countryman Davor Suker, the 1998
World Cup's top scorer with six goals. Both players helped Croatia
finish third in the competition on defeating the Netherlands 2-1.
	   (cg) 	   
</TEXT>
