<SLUG> BC-Canada-Stuntman Killed,0178 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Stuntman killed while filming television series
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SQUAMISH, British Columbia (AP) _ A Canadian stuntman died after
being hit by flying debris from a controlled explosion on the set
of the television series ``The Crow: Stairway to Heaven.''
	   Marc Akerstream, 44, was watching the filming Friday when the
exploding debris cleared a large tree and came down to strike him
on the head, police said.
	   The 15-year veteran stuntman died later at Vancouver General
Hospital. He is from Vancouver.
	   The explosion was not part of any stunt, and Akerstream was
merely a bystander, said Lauro Chartrand, a friend of the victim.
	   Authorities, including the Royal Candadian Mounted Police, were
investigating the accident.
	   It was during filming of the original movie version of ``The
Crow'' that actor Brandon Lee _ son of martial arts legend Bruce
Lee _ was killed in an on-set shooting accident in 1993.
	   The syndicated TV series, being produced by Crescent
Entertainment, is set to premiere next month.
</TEXT>
