<SLUG> BC-UN-Northern Ireland,0134 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
UN chief condemns NIreland bombing
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   UNITED NATIONS (AP) _ U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan on
Monday condemned the Northern Ireland bombing and the ``men of
violence'' who carried it out.
	   ``The secretary-general knows how deeply both communities in
Northern Ireland long to live free of the shadow of violence,''
said U.N. spokesman Fred Eckhard.
	   ``He shares the conviction of the great majority of the people
of Ireland, north and south, that change can only come about by
peaceful means.''
	   Annan condemns ``this wonton and indiscriminate act of
terrorism, and the men of violence who perpetrated it,'' he said.
	   Northern Ireland's worst-ever terrorist attack, a car bomb
Saturday in the small town of Omagh, killed 28 people.
</TEXT>
