<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-RCA Championships,0258 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Bryan wins first pro match in rain-delayed RCA
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   INDIANAPOLIS (AP) _ NCAA champion Bob Bryan won his first pro
match in Monday's rain-delayed RCA Championships, then set his
sights on top-ranked and top-seeded Marcelo Rios, his second-round
opponent.
	   Bryan ousted Steve Campbell 6-1, 0-6, 6-1 in an all-American
match that featured dramatic swings and ended shortly before a rain
shower swept across the Indianapolis Tennis Center.
	   Bryan said if he had to play the top seed, he prefers it be Rios
than Pete Sampras, who is competing this week in the Pilot Pen
International in New Haven, Connecticut.
	   ``Of all the top players, that's the one I would want to play,''
Bryan said of Rios. ``I wouldn't want to go play Sampras right now
and have him just whack serves all day at me.
	   ``I think I can play with him, and I think I'm in the point
every time,'' he said of Rios. ``He's not just going to serve me
off the court. Hopefully, I can get it rolling out there with him.
	   ``He (Rios) is a tough player; one of the world's best. It's
going to be a good opportunity, a good experience. I'm looking
forward to it.''
	   In other matches completed before rain halted play, Hicham Arazi
of Monaco stopped South African Marcos Ondruska 7-6 (7-4), 6-2;
Arnaud Clement of France ousted Paul Haarhuis of the Netherlands
6-4, 6-4; Ramon Delgado of Paraguay defeated Jerome Golmard of
France 6-3, 6-2; and Brian MacPhie stopped Spain's Jordi Burillo
6-4, 6-3.
</TEXT>
