<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Mercosur Cup-Corinthians-Racing,0170 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Corinthians seeks to extend winning streak against Racing in
</HEADLINE>
Mercosul Cup

<TEXT>
	   SAO PAULO, Brazil (AP) _ Corinthians faces Argentina's Racing on
Tuesday in a game that will give the winner first place in Group C
of the Mercosul Cup.
	   Four teams are deadlocked with one point after two ties the
opening round. Corinthians tied Paraguay's Olimpia 2-2 and Racing
drew 1-1 with Penarol of Uruguay.
	   Since club play resumed after the World Cup, Corinthians has
been on a roll. The team is undefeated in the Brazilian
first-division championship and leads the standings with 16 points.
Forward Marcelinho is the scoring leader with eight goals.
	   Coach Wanderley Luxemburgo, named this month to replace Mario
Zagallo at the helm of the Brazilian national team, will likely be
without the services of injured fullback Cris. Batata is expected
to start in his place.
	   The game starts at 9:40 p.m. (0040 GMT Wednesday) at Morumbi
stadium.
</TEXT>
