<TEXT>
	   WORLD AT 0000 GMT:
	    &UR; NEW:
	   _US-CLINTON-INVESTIGATION. Clinton admits improper relationship
with Lewinsky.
	   _UN-IRAQ. Iraq still unwilling to back down in weapons standoff.
 &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   WASHINGTON _ After months of denial, President Bill Clinton
testifies under oath that he engaged in an inappropriate
relationship with a White House intern, according to a
knowledgeable source. US-CLINTON-INVESTIGATION. Developing,
nationwide speech by Clinton scheduled at 0200 GMT. By John
Solomon.
	   WITH:
	   US-CLINTON-WORLD REACTION. Clinton's testimony invites intense _
yet mixed _ world reaction. Expected by 0200 GMT. By Martin
Fackler.
	   _ANALYSIS-US-CLINTON INVESTIGATION. Clinton confession will
erode his credibility. Has moved.
	   _US-CLINTON-FAMILY. For first family: The pain is personal.
Upcoming.
	   _US-CLINTON-WHAT'S NEXT. After Clinton's testimony, prosecutor
to report to Congress. Has moved.
	   WASHINGTON _ Russia's ruble devaluation, just a month after
promises of an additional dlrs 22.6 billion from the International
Monetary Fund, dramatically underscores the dwindling number of
solutions to halt a deepening global economic crisis.
RUSSIA-UNENDING CRISIS. Expected by 0200 GMT. By Martin Crutsinger.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _RUSSIA-ECONOMY. Amid unrelenting financial turmoil, Russia lets
ruble drop. AP Photos MOSB104,106,110-114.
	   _US-RUBLE-Q AND A. Questions and answers on the impact of
devaluation of Russia's ruble.
	   _GERMANY-RUSSIA ECONOMY. Stock markets nervous over devaluation.
	   DAR ES SALAAM, Tanzania _ U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright flies to East Africa on Tuesday, seeking to demonstrate
American support after the bombings that targeted U.S. embassies
but mostly claimed African lives. ALBRIGHT-EMBASSY BOMBINGS.
Expected by 0200 GMT; Albright arrives at 0500 GMT. By Dianna Cahn.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _EMBASSY BOMBINGS. Suspect in embassy bombings: Hot lead or dead
end?
	   _KENYA-EMBASSY IN LIMBO. Security tensions prevail at relocated
Nairobi embassy. Expected by 0300 GMT. By Dave Carpenter. AP Photos
NAI101-103.
	   OMAGH, Northern Ireland _ With all 28 victims of Northern
Ireland's worst terrorist strike identified and five suspects in
custody, families and friends prepare to say goodbye to their loved
ones Tuesday in the first of a series of funerals. NORTHERN
IRELAND. Expected by 0200 GMT; will be topped after start of
funerals at 1000 GMT. By Kristin Gazlay. AP Photos LON110,
XOGH109-110, XOMG106.
	   KINSHASA, Congo _ Faced with an army of rebels approaching
Congo's capital, President Laurent Kabila has launched a massive
drive to recruit new soldiers to defend his troubled government.
CONGO-KABILA'S RECRUITS. Expected by 0300 GMT. By Ian Stewart. AP
Photo KIN102.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _CONGO. Kabila returns to southern stronghold in struggle for
survival. AP Photos KIN101-104.
	   _CONGO-REBELS. Congolese rebels secure eastern borders; warn
civilians in their movement.
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia _ American diplomats and Yugoslav officials
confer behind closed doors to discuss ways to set up talks between
the Yugoslav government and ethnic Albanian rebels in Kosovo.
YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO. Recap expected by 0200 GMT. By Ismet Hajdari. AP
Photos PRI101-104.
	   UNITED NATIONS _ With Iraq still defiant in its standoff with
U.N. weapons experts, the Security Coucil is preparing a relatively
weak message of support for inspectors. UN-IRAQ. Recap expected by
0300 GMT. By Nicole Winfield.
	   SYDNEY, Australia _ Adventurer Steve Fossett is retrieved from
the ocean safe and sound, but his dream of flying around the world
non-stop in a balloon remains unfulfilled. BALLOON QUEST. Recap
expected by 0300 GMT. By Peter James Spielmann. AP Photos
SYD101-103.
	   NEW YORK _ A Swiss humanitarian fund will distribute more than
dlrs 31 million this fall to needy Holocaust survivors in the
United States, New York's governor announces. US-HOLOCAUST FUND.
Has moved. By Verena Dobnik.
	   KABUL, Afghanistan _ Taliban bombs hit the opposition stronghold
of Bamiyan in central Afghanistan. But the opposition alliance also
claims to be making gains. AFGHANISTAN. Lead has moved. By
Zaheeruddin Abdullah. AP Photos KAB101-102.
	   LONGYEARBYEN, Norway _ Eighty years ago, the Spanish Flu virus
killed tens of millions and then disappeared. Scientists this week
will try to pry its secrets out of an Arctic cemetery.
NORWAY-SPANISH FLU. Expected by 0200 GMT. By Doug Mellgren.
	   LOOKING AHEAD: Cuban President Fidel Castro makes his first
visit to the neighboring Dominican Republic on Friday.
 &UR; FEATURES: Business and Finance
	   NEW DELHI, India _ In the business world, they're called head
hunters. In the software trade, employment agents are called body
shoppers, and India has become a vast arcade offering new talent
seeking high paying jobs abroad. FEA-INDIA-SOFTWARE SWINDLERS.
Expected by 0300 GMT. By Neelesh Misra.
	   WOLF CREEK, Oregon _ Once sold primarily at hippie fairs and
through ads in the back pages of magazines with an environmental
bent, goods made from industrial hemp are moving into the
mainstream. FEA-US-HEMP RISING. Expected by 0300 GMT. By Jeff
Barnard. AP Photo NY180
	   GRAND RAPIDS, Michigan _ At the first mall for children,
conceived by husband-and-wife real estate developers as a tribute
to their 3-year-old son Mackie, parents shop where their kids want
to go. FEA-US-KIDS' MALL. Expected by 0300 GMT. By Lisa Singhania.
AP Photos NY181, NY182
