<HEADLINE>
Top class fleet for Olympic warm-up event
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) _ Six defending Olympic champions will
contest a sailing regatta next month to test the waters two years
out from the Sydney 2000 Games.
	   The regatta is the first of two test events for Olympic sailing
and will be held on Sydney Harbor from Sept. 19-27, the actual
dates of competition in 2000.
	   Teams from 38 nations have entered the test event, according to
a Organizing Committee spokesman, with 344 competitors across the
10 classes.
	   The Europe dinghy single-handed class has the most impressive
women's fleet led by Danish Olympic champion Kristine Roug, silver
medalist Margriet Matthysse from the Netherlands and her world
champion compatriot Carolyn Brouwer.
	   The men's Finn dinghy single-handed class will feature the
Atlanta gold and silver winners, Poland's Mateusz Kusnierewicz and
Belgium's Sebastien Godefroid, and world champion Fredrik Loof of
Belgium.
