<HEADLINE>
Phillies 4, Astros 0
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By The Associated Press &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   PHILADELPHIA (AP) _ Paul Byrd, signed only three days earlier,
outshined Randy Johnson with a four-hitter and also hit an RBI
single as the Philadelphia Phillies beat the Houston Astros 4-0
Monday night.
	   Johnson (3-1), coming off consecutive shutouts, left after the
fifth trailing 3-0. He allowed six hits and four walks, striking
out just three.
	   Byrd (1-0) had pitched only once in the majors this season,
making an ineffective relief appearance for Atlanta on April 19,
and was claimed on waivers last Friday after going 5-5 at Triple-A
Richmond. He did not permit a runner past first base, striking out
six and walking one in his first complete game in 88 career
appearances.
